\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Can you tell me your full name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Amelia. Amelia - Amelia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15020930\charrsid2379396 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 elia King?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Is - 65 Upney Lane. 65 Upney Lane, Barking, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And you're marital status? Are you a widow now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. For - thirty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You were widowed in 1940?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What year were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 1902. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Seventy - '78 I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 1878?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 That would be right wouldn't it. 1878? That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 In - would be Limehouse I suppose - Burdett Road, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Oh not very long because again as a say the shifting - mother had to shift nearer the docks for the - 'cos my brother went to sea after that. I - I can't - if I told you all you'd never get it - my mother said - s
he said she had two families. See because - she had - well three living - children very young when my father thought he would go out to South America when the work fell off he'd go out to South America to earn a - his fortune and - he - joined a company -
 I think it - whether it was a lord cup or something, to go out - Cuff - name of Cuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Lord Cuff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
I think so. I'm not sure it's Lord or - we used to say it was Lord - joined - made a company that they went to make a settlement further inland. Wel
l they were doing very well when the natives came down and - nearly - the company was more or less wiped out or scattered. Father escaped with a - spear wound in his stomach but - otherwise he wasn't hurt so he stayed a little while there to - mend his - 
his - wage, you know, to get ready to come back home and he got on a ship to come home and - the day before he came home - he was taken prisoner - political prisoner. And he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was this before you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was all before I was born. So then 
that meant that my mother went ten years before she had another - started a family when he came home again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So he was away for a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 He was away - well nearly ten years. Or a good seven years - seven to ten years. I - I can tell you the dates when I see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Can you tell me how many brothers and sisters you've got in order that they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I've got - my eldest sister - Harry - Sarah, Harry, Jack. Then there was the others died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How many others w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15020930\charrsid2379396 er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 e there in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Two 
- two died. Then - then when father came home - there was no more then - father came home there was Arthur, myself - my sister and Tom. And Willie died. So really there was seven of us left. See, three were - well, my eldest sister was like a mother to me
. When I was six he was twenty see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 She was fourteen years older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How many years were there in between your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 They had them very - she had them very quickly - mother. She had her at the twelve month, H
arry was thirteen months. Then the next were a year and five months and then the next was a year and six months. And that's all I know of the other two I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And then with your family - your brother Arthur, when was he born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 He was - he 
was born in June - two years before - be seventy-six wouldn't it - or eighty-six wouldn't it. Seventy-six. And then - the other was in December. The - the eighth of the December.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 That's the one before or after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 After me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What year would that be? You were '78 - the next one would be what year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 '76. '76 wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Arthur was '76 wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. Oh well she would be older than me wouldn't she. If I was '78 she'd be '79 or - to '80 - I couldn't tell you exactly. Then Tom w
as three years after - years younger than me so - what would he be. That's - and then Willie I couldn't tell you now exactly what year he - what his - I know he didn't live long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And the two before you didn't live either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How old do you think they lived to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh they were very young - very young in - in months. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You didn't live very long in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No, because - we went down t- Woolwich - North Woolwich - first. Then of course when we com
e back - when mother took the bigger house she - come back to poplar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Do you know how old you were when you went to North Woolwich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I suppose about two years I expect - no, I wouldn't be that - I might have been eighteen months to two years I suppose.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How old were you when you left that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 That I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were you just a little bit older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well you see - I was - whenever mother had any babies somebody took me away - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So you didn't stay with your mother all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 All the time - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did she stay in North Woolwich for many years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No, she - there was only a few - well - very few years before she came back to Poplar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Then you went back to live in Poplar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Is that the first house you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I can remember - M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15020930\charrsid2379396 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 lms - not Malms Road - what's that in Poplar where grandfather lived. See I went to school from there - I went to North - Upper North Street school from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 From Poplar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. That was in - I forget the name of the street now. It runs parallel with East India Dock Road. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Not Commercial Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No - East India Dock Road comes from the - tunnel now - 'cos the tunnel wasn't there then. I remember the tunne
l being opened. I was - up on the gallery - on a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15020930\charrsid2379396 veranda}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
 at the house, saw the opening of the - Blackwall tunnel and - then from - East India Dock Road come from there up to Burdett Road then from Burdett Road it started Commercial Road and - right up to A
ldgate and - then - I can remember the Haymarket in - in Aldgate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 That must have been very different then. You moved from North Woolwich back to Poplar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Poplar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You went to school in Poplar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. Poplar - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And you were living with your grandfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. Not - it was only about two years at the out - out - utmost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And then your mother came back there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. And we all went together then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Where did you go together then - do you remember where you lived when your mother came back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Goff Street, Poplar. Yes. Goff Street, Poplar - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh - I lived there 'til - 'til we were - I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  when I was twenty-four.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And then where did you move to - that was 1902?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. Well - well then I - I had a - house - next door but one to mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Still in Goff Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Still in Goff Street. 18. And then I - had - after that my father died - suddenly - and of course mother was still keeping her father and of 
course the other - we all got together and - mother carried on for a while, only she had - bad legs and of course - somebody had to do the rough work and all like that and - but then we - I made - I made up - I made up me mind mother and I - we'd go toget
her in a house in East Ham. Upton Park. And it was there that I had the other two - Arthur and Madge. My children, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you lived in Upton Park for many years after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No, the - we would have been - I daresay carried on very nicely onl
y - my sister made up her mind she'd go to sea with her husband, he was a Captain, and she went - sailed with him, you know, went to sea with him. So when - she'd already then got - two - grown up - a girl about sixteen - no, not so old as that and a - an
d
 a little boy. So she asked mother if she'd go and keep house - and look after these two while she was at sea. So in that case - as I say we didn't live with mother more to go with her than - though we shared everything and I took a small house for a litt
l
e while in East Ham. Carlton Avenue wasn't it. Yes. For a little while. Then - my sister was wrecked at sea - off the coast and she made up her mind she wouldn't go to sea any more so he said if you don't go I won't go. So they packed up and retired to Au
s
tralia. And - so then again mother was left. So I went into their house in Barking Road - do you know anywhere about Barking. Do you know the gas works? Well I had a house - the house was right opposite. Yes. It's different to what - when we lived - we ha
d front garden see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 They're widening the road now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Are they? Well - they altered it all - oh two or three years ago, they took all the pillars away from the doorway and made it all white or - didn't look nice at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was it before the first world war that you moved there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Oh yes. We went in 1912 I think. 1912? '11 or '12 but I can't exact - but I know we went all through the war in that house - the first world war. Yes. And then - I was there - we were there 'til we came here in - '83. 
So we've been here just on fourty years haven't we. Nearly forty years - two more years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Let me see - they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
 very young I know - my mother was - mother was for - thirty-six when I was born so he'd be about thirty-seven I suppose. Thirty-seven - thirty-eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 He was at Poplar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 He was a local born Poplar man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes, see near the docks you see, his father was a - a Scotsman. I couldn't - I could give you lo
ts of romantic stories attached to the - I suppose we can't go into that. So his father was a - a Scotsman brought up very well in - in - in Aberdeen and he ran away to sea and then of course they drift along, he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  an English girl and he had - five s
ons and one daughter. Or two daughters. So he wasn't - when his mother died he wasn't comfortable and he left home and he - went to lodge with one of my uncles. He'd just lost his wife, he got a home and he - he - the two went together. That's how he got 
- I suppose - mother got - acquainted. I can't tell you the - all the - those - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What was his occupation.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well a shipwright you see at first then he went to sea as a ship's carpenter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 A shipwright is somebody who makes.....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Used to build the ship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Is it a skilled job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Oh yes. Oh yes. They used to say that the shipwrights ate their soveraigns with - ate their butter with sovereigns, with - ate their butter with sovereigns, you know, it's so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When that finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
It didn't finish altogether because they couldn't do without certain amount of staging, you know, when ships went into dry dock they had to make the staging for them to go round the ship even when they were high - well they 
do up to now. And - he - he was a - as I say he went to sea as a ship's carpenter. Well - if there is anything went wrong on the ship you know - breakages in bad weather he was there to repair the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When he came back from this ten years abroad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did he do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 That's when he went to sea as a ship - as a - a - a ship's carpenter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Can you remember him having any other kind of job after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, he was there on the - he died suddenly on board ship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Still working as a carpenter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Yes. He was never - he came home on the Wednesday and was going to sail - sail on the Saturday to take the place of another ship and he died on the Friday. He went on board - bid mother goodbye at the door and said he'd be home at fo
ur o'clock and he went straight onto the ship - went into his cabin to change his clothes - because you know - merchant people are not supposed to wear any uniform ashore, but anyhow he - he was - went - changed his clothes, got his boot in his hand to pu
t on his boot and fell forward dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 He was - 1903.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did he also do any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Do you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes. There was that time - he was twelve years in the 
one ship. And - when that ship was sold - he was - and the company - the company dissolved see he - he got - what was it - the Bucknell Brothers had - had a ship in - in Bucknell Brothers going to South Africa. And then - he - somebody said that - having 
short of voyages so he went into Hall's Line. T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15020930\charrsid2379396 hat was the - take up the Medit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15020930\charrsid2379396 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 ranean the fruit - bringing the fruit home - oranges and s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15020930\charrsid2379396 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 ltanas and all that sort of thing. And it was in that line when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Mother was born in - Limehouse or Stepney, I forget. I now she was christened in Stepney church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Had she any jobs before she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 She was a dressmaker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did she work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Only while father was away. Well when - wh
en he was in - when he was taken prisoner there was no money coming in at all. So she had to do - turn to and - do best she could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did she do dressmaking then or did she have any other kind of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, no. She used to go - she went into a - one 
of these ready made dressmaking places. See - 'cos she had no connection - she went in there, used to work piece work. Up - up to the time I was born she didn't do anymore after that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When she was working do you know who looked after the children for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - grandfather Selby, that was on my father's side took my eldest sister and - mother had the - grandma Miller had the two boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I think we'd better concentrate on the house in Goff Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Goff Street. It's Goff Park there - it's altered. Goff Park now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Can you tell me how many rooms there were in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 That was four - eight rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What were the different rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well there's a kit - a kitchen, we used to call it a breakfast room, the two parlours, the
n the two best bedrooms and the two above - well, they were more on the attic style you know, the - the back was all right but the front had a little bit of a slant. So that was the eight rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did anyone else besides your parents and your brothers and sisters live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
