hese different factories bought their people with them and there was a big furniture - on one of the - right at the bottom Stainsbury Road I think it was a big furniture - near the canal you know, so as they can get things away - and - they brought all th
e
 Germans over for cheap labour. See. And then - all the - like such as our houses - or not so much our - but most six roomed houses they'd take over - like the foreigners do now and let off in the one room at a time you see. It - that - but I don't think 
