\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I should say better - class working people. 'Cos my husband was a mechanic. But all the others - I was the one that }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  - worse off. Yes. Dad would never have got anything more than a working - 
mind he was a piece worker - piece - done by - worked by piecework, only earnt what he - only had paid
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 what he earned, which nearly killed him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What class would you think your father was?
