\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Would be mostly - people in - some in decent positions and they may - one of my uncles was a foreman in a silver refiners. He had a position lived in the firm, now what would you - he would only be a working man after all wouldn't he. No, the
 working class that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 It's very difficult isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Yes. Different - but of course being seafaring we got mixed up with a lot. You see - now there was James Arthur, he was a - he was - had - a manager of the mills out in India, our - Jute m
ills. Well of course he made his fortune and he retired. Well he remained a staunch family - hiss - his brother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
 my eldest sister. See, so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Would you put him in a separate class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well he would be - all - esquire you would say 'cos he - he retired when he was forty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Would you put him in a higher class then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes - oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 We're all alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were you ever told to curtsey or show respect in anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. Not curtsey, I never curtsied in me life. I should fall over on me nose I think. I knew how to behave myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was there anyone you called Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I don't think I - no, I don't think I did. I 
always used to say Mr Kirkcaldy even - Mr James I used to call him 'cos he was one of the - family of Kirkcaldy's. There was Mr James, Mr John, Mr Pat, Mr Adam. They were one big family but all very - they had - started in engineering, the ship's engineer
i
ng. And then one broke out into this paint - got out a patent for - for ship's well he went one way and another one went another - two went as professor in - from college. But - that there was a big far - but Mr James I used to call him Mr James. But he w
as - very fond of my husband. Right up to my husband's death. He kept correspondence with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these says?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. Always the proper Mr and Mrs but never by, as they do now, by a Christian name
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 In the district who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - would be - all much of a muchness - there was schoolteachers - doctors all round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Do you know why they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - they did a lot of good didn't they, most - giving - well they had surgeries then, there was no -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Who did the doctors associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I suppose with the - no, you see, with the KirkCaldy's and the Corners, they inter-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 . Again - Corners was the best class doctors in Poplar, well one of the Kirkcaldy's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  a Miss Corner, see, that's how it went on and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What about teachers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well my niece was a teacher so she associate - she associated with me. Well we knew severa
l teachers but - you know - just friendly. Well that class we - we would be in you'd say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What about clergymen, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - we didn't go to - to Church of England, we were more - Angelical - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Evangelical?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What about employers - the ones that owned the factories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh there's a big company up in Chelsea where my husband worked. Glovers, I don't know whether they're there yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 But who did the employers in your district mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh - couldn't say - they'd be away. Kirkcaldy's - well, yes, they moved didn't they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Who would they have mixed with socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well they would mix with doctors and solicitors and - the clergy, see, the man that - the vicar that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  me - my - me and my husband, he was a friend of the Kirkcaldy's therefore I had a - we had a special service, though I wasn't Church of England. Dad was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What sort of people would you say went to the church and what sort of people went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I -
 we were mixed. Some people - if there was a Church of England school - which there were many in those days and the children went to the school they belonged to the church as well, you see. Of course we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What about the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well the chapel wasn't very far away and - they - they were more - on the level with us you might -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say that there were different groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well there were some people very - there was a - a bank manager - little way away and next door to us when we first went to number twenty-two were nuns, I don't know where they went to after that, I forget but - and another was a - a - one - one side wa
s the family where my younger brother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
 the little girl and then further on was - a retired - engineer, you know, that used to do these big - bri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4744601\charrsid2379396 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
ges and that and he'd retired and then there was teachers further along. All - that was a very nice type of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Would you say they all had a similar standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes, I - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was there anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - I - some of them would be better standards - the - the bank manager and his two sons - they all went to - up to the City of t
heir high hats and frock coats in those days. That type. Very - they were - we never got - you know - not shaking hands, just good morning and that far and the - and opposite - was a clergyman lived opposite.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I think you said before that most of the people were respectable in your area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was there anybody you would have said wasn't respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. None at all - except when - as I say - the Germans came over, they took a house and let off but I don't know - we came away at that ti
me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your mother and father have the same sort of attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Just the same I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, do you think so? She was very knowledgeable person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
