d at Burdett Road then - then it was Commercial Road up to Aldgate wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was that the poorer part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, East India Dock Road was very nice. Commercial Road began to get poor and then u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4744601\charrsid2379396 p further along got - more Jewey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 fied. But - as - as the -
 East India Dock Road come like that and then West India Dock Road went that - that's were you got the - the rough part - the Chinese and all those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 They were thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And the others were respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. Yes. It - t
hat Poplar was in two parts. There were some very nice parts and there were some very - Poplar and Limehouse was nice but further down was - as it got worse, you know, with the different - you know, got mixed up with - foreigners coming in, you know, the 
sailors.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, I didn't remember seeing them. My -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Do you know what sort of a landlord he was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh - well - to tell you the truth it was sold over head and i
t was Duretta's the engineers in Limehouse and when he died he left the - our house to - his daughter. Wel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4744601\charrsid2379396 l she wanted to - the house for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  herself so that's the cause of me mother and I going together you see. She wanted it for herself so they come to the conclusion see all ours was - I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  and - Doll was going to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  and the boys - the others were all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  and away that was - wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4744601\charrsid2379396 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  only}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4744601\charrsid2379396  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
mother, grandfather and - Uncle Arthur - even Tom was away, so with that mother had five rooms and she had three and they lived like - but it wasn't comfortable so that's why we all went together in Barking Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Before she took over did you feel that your landlord was a good landlord or a bad landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - if you - we didn't - Well you'd sa
y he was a good landlord 'cos we paid - mother used to pay monthly as her money came monthly, she put that by for the rent and - but we were very - the boys would turn to and do things - repairs in the house. Such as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I daresay at times she did do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did you think about it as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I'll tell you - I've heard my mother say that - when he first came home from - South America, after being a - a prisone
r, well all that time mother had a job to make ends meet with of course, with the help of her friend - her relations, 'cos she didn't have a penny piece and - more than your life was worth ever to go to the parish for relief in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well if you - you was never allowed to vote - lost your vote or anything - you became - oh - what would you call it - yes - if - if you ever went. Because when my father died my grandfather was so upset knowing he never had anything to give mother, he was
 living on mother, he went down to the guardians and said could they give him any relief so they said yes, if you come in - you'll have to come into the workhouse for three days and live in and then you can claim. Well then you'd lose your vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did he do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No. My mother - my mother went nearly frantic because the very relieving officer came to mother says, Mrs Selby, he says, do you know your father Mr Miller come here come to us asking - oh mother was upset.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever have to have anything from the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 She managed even when he was away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
YES. And when father died of course we all - we all - kept together, helped each toher. Well - mother - the boys was earning and - of course when father died of course h
e - he worked 'til he did die and - it was - wasn't much chance of saving - we got a comfortable home and all that sort of thing and she brought us all up respectable that - she - the boys all promised - there was four boys then - Narry, Jack - Narry and 
Jack o Tom and Arthur all going to give her ten shillings a weak. See that'd be two pound a week. Well in those days that was very good. I don't say she always got it but still - they - they made her - that's what they -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So you managed between you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Between us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Relieving officers weren't very well regarded then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Oh no. No. Oh was disgraceful if you did that. But fancy him doing that - of course he was over eighty then you see and he'd never gone to the parish before. To think of su
ch a thing but - I suppose he was upset the same as - everybody else with coming on you sudded like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were you given lessons by one of your parents when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, my eldest sister 'cos she was training at one time for a tea
cher, my eldest sister. She kept - kept me us so I never went to school 'til I was seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You didn't go to school 'til you were seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Is this Sarah that taught you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 At home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 At your grandparent's home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did she teach you regularly every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well - not - used to be - I suppose when she could - she could sit down and talk to me and - as I say, I could go all through my tables right up to twelve times table before I was seven. That - th
at's a repetition. Then she gave us the - there was the sums, you know - add - multiplication - multiplication is vexation, division is as bad, the rule of three trouble me and practice drives me mad. They don't know what practice is now do they. Practice
 sums. How - one time when Malcom was going to college - how do you do practice sums. He said practice, what do you mean by practice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have lessons alone with your sister or did she teach others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - I was - see I was living with her wh
en she gave me most of the - lessons, you know, when I was - between eight and nine. Oh no, eight - seven - six to seven you get mixed up a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you go to school after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Then I went to school when I was seven. But I never went in the infants, I went straight into the girls school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What time in the morning did you go and what time did you come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well went in at - supposed to be in at - in the classroom at nine o'clock and left at twelve in the morning. Then you went in - of 
course you'd be beforehand - two o'clock 'til half past four in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What kind of school was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was a - well would have been in those days a modern school. It's standing yet, in North - Upper North street. Infants down below, the boy
s are next and the girls on top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was it a Church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No. Board - well I suppose it wasn't a school board then, I don't know what it was I can remember the London school board 'cos we - we had to pay a - pay to go. I used to pay three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 pence 'cos I was the first to go, the others only paid tuppence each so that was - mother be - have to pay nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 pence a week school money. And - then of course free education, that made some of the Tories scratch their heads. More rates to pay on the rates. Oh de
ar. Well - well I suppose it would be more on the rates wouldn't it. Well - the - free edu - oh that was free education wasn't it. Well then I went on until I got into the sixth standard and then of course mother's serious illness, well - as I say, father
 was at sea, I had - mother had the couch in the kitchen and told me what to do and - I had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So you stopped school when you were thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Thirteen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 There were boys and girls in this school but they weren't together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You didn't have lessons with the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No. The bottom was infants, the next was the boys - the top was girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 We had to walk. It didn't take us - by cutting in between - we would go so far in our - in
 Goff Street, through a little turning into Kenton Street, out of Kenton Street into Pekin Street, into North Street. I could do it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Would this take ten or fifteen minutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I daresay about ten minutes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 We w
ent on our own. See, as I say, Hetty Skeins used to call for me or I'd call for Hetty Seins, we'd go together and - be the same coming home you see. When Tom was younger he started school earlier 'cos we were all in Poplar then, somebody'd take him to sch
ool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Would you take him or would your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I would take him I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you come home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did you think of school - did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I liked it. Very fond of school. I d - w
ish I could have had more education. I was sorry that I - but I - mother's - I used to say, now can I - let me be apprenticed to the dressmaking, mother, I said, the boys have all had a good education, she kept them 'til sixteen, they boys had a good educ
ation at school and they were all - all got apprentices. Well mother said that's their living, girls marry for their future. That was my future - get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Could you have stayed on at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I could have stayed on if -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 At that school or would you have had to have tone to another one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No, I could have - up to - well I should have only had another year - fourteen. Then they transfers you to - if you - clever enough you could go to the - well I suppose - higher - higher grade, li
ke scholarship girls would go there. Like my - my younger brother went to Thomas Street from our - our school, we all went to the one school and when we got to - to the fourth standard - sixth standard - seventh standard we - and he passed the scholarship
 he was sent to this Thomas Street school. And he was there til the seventh - sixteen and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh I liked them very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did they emphasise certain things as important in life - like manners or tidiness or punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well I - as I say with religion I do like it in school because a good teacher would explain it to you when we had a - the religious lesson, they'd explain it to you far better than you would be in a - in a church or chapel. If you 
got a good teacher. And I really - I think - more religion to sink in than ever I did anywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What about manners and way of speaking and tidiness - did they emphasi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396 z}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 e these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes, they would - oh I don't suppose they would allow 
you to be untidy, they were always - always a nice tidy - that went to the school - there wouldn't be any untidiness. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were the other children from similar sorts of him to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. There were - some were a little bit more rough and tumble 
but - some were higher, some went to - got good scholarships out of the fourth standard where - where they started training and I know now their names - Alice Durham and - something - I forget their names just now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What do you mean by some were rough and tumble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well, you know, more careless in their behaviour, you know, would - wouldn't listen to all - have to be corrected, you know. And have - have been brought out in front of the class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Would you say they came from rougher homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I should think so. Might have been, yes. Nothing out of the way but - you know, not so - so particular in their manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And they were corrected by the teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well - if it was very bad she'd send us to the governess and she would talk to us. Or - and sometimes they would give you - a - I suppose writing to stop in to do writing. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were you ever smacked or caned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No - I was only caned onc
e - once and that was through staying away. Not - not - mother kept me away - I should have taken a note instead of that I went without a note so - it was warned if we stayed away from school we've got to have a - a note from your parents to - the reason 
why you were away from school. Well evidently I went without - I can't tell - I hadn't got the note and I know I had the cane on the hand and I never forgot it. I thought to myself, I'll never have it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did girls get it as well as boys then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What other things would they get the cane }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 or?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well if they were rude I think - boys would be more - unruly, they might get - caning I don't - well they would have, trust a boy. He wouldn't always be good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your parents show any interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes, as far as - as possible but they were never encouraged like they are now. To go to the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did they ever go to the school and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No. No, I don't - of course, the governess at the school where I went, my eldest sister she was a - a pupil teacher the same time as - my sister - my sister was training - beginning to train and this Miss Eastland was a pupil teacher above her so the
y knew each other, that's all - got in contact with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Only these two very clever girls. They were single out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
I tell you there's in - in - you have a yearly examination and if you didn't pass whether you were good or bad you had to stop in another year, you see, that's how it came about. That's one thing I never failed. Every year I passed but - it - bu
t if I'd have - say I was going from third standard into - fourth and I - hadn't passed I'd have to keep two years in one standard. It wasn't fair. No - it - it didn't affect me but - it did - would have done Edie wouldn't it if I hadn't have gone and - I
 did have a row with that - her teacher but that was my niece.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were there any gangs or groups of children in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh the boys used to have school fights. One school against the other. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What about among themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were there any children from the workhouse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No. No, no, they - they had a school of their own. Workhouse children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you attend any part time education after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I did once or twice, went - went to evening class as they called it but - but I never kept it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did you go to evening classes for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well they - they - for b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 tany and all those sort of things. Well that wasn't doing the much good - I - I liked it but - if they'd have given me dress making I should have liked it better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396 Do you think you benefit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 ed from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 But - evening class or ordinary? Oh yes. Oh I - I liked school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little pocket money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When you left school you stayed at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I can't - I should - sixteen or seventeen I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When you were about sixteen or seventeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 It was - to go in the desk in a - provision - place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You told me about this before didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 About Lipton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 s?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 This was a provision shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. And I was in the desk taking the money. And keeping books and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - this - friend of - I told you, that mother - mother and grandmother - they - one of the girls went to the - she went to this }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396 \endash  Lip}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 ton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 s and she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 spoke for me and I went in there. They took me on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What exactly did you have to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well you see - in - was a - same as it is now, they had the - the check books, one half for the customer and the other half they would bring to the desk and I'd have to put it on a file and give the correct change, see, 
and - then every night I had to collect up the - the takings and give to the manager.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 One week - two weeks were from nine 'til - nine 'til nine or - yes nine 'til nine. And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396  the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  week was from eight 'til seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Sundays did you have to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, not Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Saturdays up 'til twelve o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have any other half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Thursday, yes. Yes. Oh very often we would put in the seventy-two hours a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What were you paid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I started with eight shillings a week. And had to - had to take charge of pounds and pounds but did enough to keep you honest though.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I - it was just that it was a little extra pocket money that was all me own then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You didn't give any of that money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. Well I might have given her something or - or bought her something out of it from the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I used to buy me own clothes then. Or put something towards me own clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Why did you take the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I thought I'd like to - well Doll was at home then, leaving school - mother didn't want two girls at home on her hands so -
 I - but - see, soon as I turned up sick Doll took my places, she went out to work and I stopped at home again, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So how long were you at Lipton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 s?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh about a couple of years I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Very well - but hard work it was for - long hours and - and then you had to keep the - books, you know, entries of the stores and all like that and sometimes you had to get out and help unpack some of the things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How did your employers treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well you didn't know the employer - was a big - a big - like - would be - as they are now, these - multiple places. He had them all over the country. Lipton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8205727\charrsid2379396 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 s. They gradually - Sir Thomas Lipton you've heard of him - he - he retired of course and he - he lost all his money trying to beat the Americans didn't he. Sailing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What was your manager like?
