 was like a clock itself - very - fine work to do. He - he was pretty well steady on that. But - you wouldn't believe the squabbles over that you know, and they - it was the men that - that lost time - lost all that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So he was a bit fed up with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Oh yes, yes. But he was - oh he - he would go when the doctor said he wasn't fit to go he would go didn't he - Alec - he's dropped off you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Who? Well I had the three of them didn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You had three children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Can you tell me their dates of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Alec was - April the sixth 1903 wasn't it. The other was - Arthur was third of February 1907 wasn't it - '07, yes. Madge was February the fifth, 1907. Two years after. 1909, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were your children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you know what to expect in childbirth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Did I - I knew what to expect - what I had to put up with beforehand. But - if - no, I knew it was going to be a bad time and I - I made up - I got through it all right, very - always had bad time afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What do you mean, because of what went on beforehand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - I used to have kind of fits when I had - well you shy and men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 tra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396 di}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 tions you know, used to have fits that caused me to not to be able to go out to work much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have any medical help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
What? Oh yes. I had the doctor - our own family doctor that used to attend to me beforehand and he was expecting I'd have it worse than what it was but still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your husband help?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 In the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 At the time when you had babies - how soon were you out of bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well they usually got you out - at the eight day I think and then you remain in bed the ninth day and the tenth you got up - that was the rule, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Eight days in bed all the time, the ninth day you got up for a little while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How did you manage while you were in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh we had a - used to have a - what they called monthly nurses - women that knew a little of - of - sickness, you
 know, widow or anything like that or - person that - could afford - got the time to come out. You'd pay them so much a week and they slept in the house with you, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So they'd stay there all that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 They - yes, they - they washed the baby and - washed the - nappies and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did any of your relations or neighbours help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No, not while they were there. Might help - mother would help - come in afterwards. And - the neigh - you used to have - engaged for a fortnight 
or three weeks according to how the funds were. The first one was three weeks and the next was only two weeks and the next was only two weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How did you feed your first baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh breast baby. All of them were breast fed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you enjoy feeding the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - it's better than having to wash bottles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have any difficulties in feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No. No, no feed - no trouble at all and - I didn't believe in - giving them anything solid, no more than a little - a crust or - yo
u know, to gnaw or - little gravy, little bread in the gravy sometimes now and again. But I never fed them, not - not potatoes and that 'til they - 'til I - about nine months then I'd start and finish them off the breast at twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 About nine months you started giving them the solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Yes, after nine months I started giving - not really all - only very light food and give - kept them - give them a breast feed at - going to bed, see, 'til - when I found they slept well I didn't give them that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was this gradual or sudden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Gradual. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did the baby mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, I never had any - much trouble, no. I had more trouble getting rid of me milk. You see, the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 If you needed advice who did you ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I should - either mother or - go to the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 If they baby was asleep would you wake it for a feed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I didn't - no. I - I was - I wasn't regular, not with the - children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 If it cried before the normal time would you feed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I wouldn't - if
 - if - I used to do - give - bath them in the morning when - as soon as got up, bath them and change them and give 'em a feed and put them down to sleep. Then - they'd sleep and then when they - wo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 e up well they - perhaps play with their fingers or have 
a yell or something like that and then they'd have a - have their breast feed and then they'd have a sleep, well when they're very young they sleep more than anything don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 But if it did wake up quite quickly and started crying before it was time to be fed again would you feed it or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, I - take it up and I thought it had enough see what was the matter with it. Might - might have a pin somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did you do if it didn't seem hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - I don't know. It always seemed to be ready as far as I can - oh Jim was never hungry baby but the other one was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How long would you let it go on feeding? ;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well they seemed to be satisfied then you take it away. I didn't do any special - not like they do now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you think at the time that id did any harm to be a baby to let it cry or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well they should cry for - to expand their lungs for a little while shouldn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you punish it when it was naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh - couldn't punish them when they're young like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 As they got older to the toddler age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Oh tell 'em they were naughty. Say they're naughty but I don't believe in - only once ever that I did ever smack Madge and that was - she was sickening for the measles and I didn't - I wasn't well myself and - I - wanted to get on with - I had me stair}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
carpet down and I want to get it back again and - she was - you know, that grissly, grissly and I said, oh do stop it. She was only about two - two or two and a half and her - I give her - I said, now cry for something and I sma}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
ked her arm. Poor little kiddie - oh I've never forgotten it. The next - when I went to bath her at night time she was out on the chest with measles so she was - wanted cuddling you know, comforting and wanted me to pick her up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So you felt very sorry for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I did feel sorry - I felt sorry for myself too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How much did your husband have to do with your children when they were babies under a year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh don't - he didn't like babies. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did he feed them or bath them or change their nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No. Oh not when they were young like that but he always took the two boys, always bathed them didn't he. They had the luxury - you see, Peter would - bath them in front of the fire in a zinc bath the bo
ys, I'd take the girls up into the bathroom into the bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 But he never changed their nappies or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh dear no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did he play with them when they were babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, very little. He wasn't a baby lover at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did he ever attend to them in the night? Or take them out in their prams?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
He wouldn't walk beside me with the pram. No, he wasn't a man for babies at all. But once they began to walk about he took notice of them and would play - would - well not - he would
 sing to them and - and do things like that. Wouldn't he? Well he ought to remember but - it - he wasn't a great one at - well, see he hadn't the - his time was from six in the morning 'til six at night come home have a meal I'd try and get them to bed be
f
ore he came in, see, so he didn't have much time when they were young but - he - of course he was different as they got older. Quite companionable. He did the right thing in - taught them how to behave and all the rest of it and gave them good advice as t
hey got on and - he wouldn't - he would - he didn't like them be out after eleven o'clock at night unless they were going anywhere
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you know what your husband earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Couldn't say at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How much of what he earned would he give to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well we had a settled - I had a settled income - housekeeping money, see, and if - if he didn't earn it and - I had to go short if he - sometimes he would make it up, sometimes he didn't but I was supposed to have a certain - housekeeping money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you discuss with your husband how the money would be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Never - we trusted each other I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You said that there were four rooms in the house you lived in at Goff Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. Six roomed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did any relatives live with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No, I did let off two rooms to a young }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  couple - for a while and then - you know - 'cos it was - good rent for - in those days - fourteen shillings a week was - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Fourteen shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. For a week rent. 'Cos rent then was very cheap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you only have Alec then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Had Alec and then - Arthur was a few weeks old when I moved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. Oh only a girl - a young girl would come in - and - like take the - them out for a -
 in the pram or she would - as she got older she would help me clean up the cutlery at the weekend you know, those weekend jobs. Never - I couldn't afford it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you pay her for doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes, yes. Can't remember now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 She just came at weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did you call each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh - well she called me Mrs King I su}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396 ppose. I called her by her C}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 hristian name.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I done it all - I done it myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were the clothes and mended by your or your husband - did you take any clothes or mend then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
I made - made all the clothes that could be made. Like he bought his suits and - of course when they got old enough we bought their suits but - I used to make their knicker
s and - knit their pullovers oh and I - oh there was one - one wedding I forgot to tell you about my sister's wedding, but that don't matter. He was a - a little - one of a little boys all in white with the other cousin you know that I told you, he was - 
the two of them were there with their sticks with - they had white tunic suits, white socks and white hats. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you or your husband make or mend shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 If you bought shoes or clothes were they new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh - new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Where were they bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Mostly - as I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396  told you there was a - a child}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  - in - I forget - I remembered it the other night, I've forgotten it now but most of it - Roberts in Stratford, I believe it's now the Co-op's taken it over, I'm not sure. Roberts
 and - and also Boardmans, yes. Bought a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When did they have new clothes or shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 For - all according to when they kicked them out. But you - but of course - I used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
had a sailor blouse or something in the summertime and knickers and of course suits in the winter and overcoats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your husband mend the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No, he wasn - wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12990931\charrsid2379396 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 n't handyman at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you mend them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did he help with any jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No, I used to be carpenter and do
 what I - if there was anything - I had a set of tools and I - we had a set of tools from mother's and I'd do any little - put up a shelf or anything like that. Or I'd get my brother - my elder brother two years older than me, he'd do any jobs like that f
or me. No, dad was no good in that. Well he had no time really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did he light any fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh he lights fires. Oh he - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did he ever do any cooking or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, not then. Did at the latter part of his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 But you said that he bathed the two boys? Did you say he old them stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes, he'd tell 'em about his pranks when he was a boy and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did he ever take the children out without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - they took them to see the Trooping of th
e Colours and brought them home all drowned - it was a wet day. The two boys but - oh - ooh he'd take then for a walk, he was very proud of them when - when they were - you know, got older and nicely dressed, oh he'd take them for walks then, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did he ever look after the children while you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I never - very seldom went out. No. He - he wasn't a - he wasn't a family man, no. He was a kind man but he wasn't a family man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were there any regular household tasks for the children to help you with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - he used to clean knives, you know, we didn't have stainless knives then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Alec used to clean knives? ;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. And Edith could help me wash down the dressers 'cos you I know I told you we had - even when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  we had dressers in my - pretty long dressers but not - not such a big one as mother's. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Could you tell me who Edith was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 She was my husband's brother's child. His wife died and then she was three years old and he was a sailor - was a steward goin
g to sea. He put her out to somebody to look after her and she got neglected - got a dirty head and one thing and the other. And - he - nobody wanted her. She was rather a crosspatch a - poor little child, losing her mother - that nobody wanted her. Even 
h
er own mother's family wouldn't have her. And - he come - he was going - got to that - pitch that he would have put her in a - you know - kind of an orphanage and pay - pay for her but we knew it would never do because he was one of those, when he came ho
m
e he'd want her out, see, to take her - you know - for the time being, though he never really did her any good in a way he never - talked to her nicely to bring her up so - I said to mother, I don't like the idea I - poor Lou is - her mother I knew - was 
f
riendly with me, I said, what - if poor Lou knew, I said, I can't - I think I'll take her. So - I did. I said, I'm not going to have any more - I've go two boys. He was a quiet boy and Arthur was only a little baby - about - about seven months old and so 
I - thought - felt free to take her and - from that time - I - kept her right the way up, saw her tight through schooling, got her out to - her first job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 She lived with you all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 All the time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your husband agree?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You didn't legally adopt her did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No. No. No. I was still called aunt - Auntie Millie - all her - all her life. I wouldn't have here call me mother because - I wasn't her mother so she called me Auntie Millie and when my - Madge was
 born she was about - I'd had her then about two or three - two years - oh, she went crazy after this baby and that was the only; time that brought any love into her life. Then she was an affectionate girl and she - loved that Madge up to the time of her 
death. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 They were very close?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you say that the two girls had regular jobs to do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Madge and Edith.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well Edie didn't like work - I didn't give her anything to do much, except like helping me - I 
- washing up I'd say you - you do the wiping up before you go to school. She always had an attack to go to the lavatory. So I finished up doing it all myself. But I never grumbled at her. And of course - then they had a good way to walk to their school. B
ut it's a shame to make them late so I did it all myself and of course at that - then at that time I was able to - between us like - have a woman in you know, half a day, see, Tuesdays and Friday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So later on you were able to have someone in to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What time did the children go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well as I told you before in the young days I tried to get them to bed before my husband came home, of course he would be half past six. To seven - if I could get them to bed beforehand, or perhap
s Alec might be up but the two younger ones I'd always get to bed. 'Cos a man don't want yarned children when they come home to a meal and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Do you know what age they put themselves to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I don't - can'
t ever remember them - my Madge - you - that was - she - she was about three - three - no, when the war started if - she'd be about - five I think - no, wouldn't be so old as that - four - four, she would dress down - undress downstairs I used to have sle
e
ping - not nightgown, you know, pyjamas all in one, you know, jump into the arms and pull up the - that - I used to put them to warm and let her undress herself and she was so methodical, folding her clothes, each thing as she took off she'd fold it then 
she'd tuck them under her arm and then she'd walk up to bed and get into bed herself. The boys, either dad might have seen them up to bed. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What was the sleeping arrangements for the family when you had all four of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - see I - the - t
wo boys was in one room, little room, I had the big - mother had the big front room - and I had the back. So that would be - see the house was one very big front room - went over the hall, that was mother's room, then we had the next room, then the girls 
and the boys in the - the two - the two small rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did they share a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Yes. Until - it got on - after mother died that I went into the front room and - the girls had separate - beds then, in the back room 'cos there was room for it and then t
hat end room where the boys had - they had separate beds. I remember I bought just before I came here I bought - iron - enamelled white with a - up that shape and oh they were - it was a pretty room and when we came here they wouldn't have these iron beds
, they wanted - wanted oak beds. Well - they had to help me out with the - with - they chose them they had to help me out with - so they had oak beds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What room was used for bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 The children? Downstairs - the two boys? Oh they were - they'd 
do it in front of the kitchen fire if I took their - the girls upstairs into the bathroom then they went straight to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Where did the girls have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Separate bathroom, yes. Yes. From the time I left Poplar I always had a bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When did they have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Usually Friday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When did they have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well the - they'd have it on the Sunday as a rule. Oh would put on clean underclothes right away - the clean vests and their clean nightdresses and then - of course on Sunday whatever - clean petticoats according to what they were going to wear.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Where were meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - when we was - when they were little we used to have it in the kitchen. But as they - as they grew older we used to have them i
n the back parlour and - course it - in Barking Road here it was all in one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Where did you cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
In the kitchen or the scullery. See in Barking Road there's the two parlours then there's this - a big kitchen then a scullery and beyond that was - had a glasshouse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you cook on gas or a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - gas. There was a gas stove there. 'Cos I'd been used to the gas after the explosions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room apart from the kitchen or scullery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well in the back parlour we - well we did used to do that. We'd have breakfast in kitchen but I - I always - in the other front or the back parlour whichever - was occasions - we used to have - always have a change of food - you know, not to have - time y
ou cooked it in the kitchen or the scullery - smelly so we go to into the room for a change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Your husband went off at six o'clock so did he have breakfast on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well sometimes we used to get up and help him but - give it to him, but otherwi
se he wasn't a big eater - he could - just have - tea and - a egg or something like that. I used to - sometimes if I wasn't - if I was all right I get up and give him his breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And did the rest of the family have their breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 O
h by that time I called them - I'd call them up and then - in the meantime I'd get mother's - while mother was alive I'd cook her breakfast and one of them would take it up to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did you usually eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Tea - mostly tea. And - as I say, the children used - when they were very young would have a - bread and milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have anything different on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What - for breakfast? Well - they'd have bread and milk first and then I'd give 'em a little piece 
of - cook some bacon - and give 'em a piece of bacon on bread or - or - no tomatoes in those - much in those days but - be an - another time with egg cheap we'd have an egg each. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did you have at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I always cooked the two vegetables, what was in season - sometimes a pie or pudding or - or a little piece of - little joint. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What members of the family were home for the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh would be only the children, mother and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What about the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 E
vening meal. Well the children wouldn't have much more than - bread and butter, cake and - watercress or anything like that. Not a - a heavy meal, not while they was at school, then of course they'd have the - have their homework to do and - or went out f
or a little while. I don't think they went very much out unless they went to other school chums' houses exchange you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have anything different to eat on Sundays for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Always a joint - always a joint of some kind. Whatever was
 doing and - and - tea - tea there was, you know, jam, watercress, lettuce if - all according what's in season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you make your own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. Well - no, I didn't because - my h
usband wasn't that way inclined for jams or pickles or anything that I never did it myself - I bought it. Bought them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever make wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. As I'd told you we used to have the casks then when it got bottles we'd have bottled beer come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you make any medicines yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No. What was that - liquorice powder - well there was a time when they made it into a kind of a - a - a jam in little pots - about that - that - give that to the children or - senna - senna leaves - 
senna pods, put then in a jug and - half a pound or a pound of raisins and pour boiling water on that, then when it got cold every morning give 'em a - one glassful of - those eat the most - those that drank the most - plums got the biggest tummy ache.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you grow fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did I ...? No, I didn't have stuff - in Barking Road there was a very small back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Tinned
 fruit, yes, used to have the tinned fruit - we tried to have the fresh fruit when you could have - apples and - apples you could have really almost the year round but - we used to gooseberries was - rhubarb was first, gooseberries, then cherries and plum
s. But - as the season went through I always had the fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you keep any livestock for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I think nearly all through the - sometimes we'd have a fish - a day. Not - we wasn'
t Catholics to have it on Friday but - we'd have it one day a week and usually ended up on Saturday with sausages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Tinned meat? Sometimes we'd have some corned beef, yes, hot weather when we didn't want to cook.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever have to go short so that your children or husband could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your husband need to have larger helpings of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, he was a poor eater. He wasn't a strong man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were the children allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes, we let them - as long as they behaved themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Could they choose what they wanted to eat or did they have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I used to put - give - serve them with everything and if they didn't like to eat
 it well they left it but - I wouldn't force them to have it and I wouldn't keep it away from them. I do know that Edith, my niece, she would never eat turnips. But I put it on her plate if we cook it. Whatever I was cooking I'd give it to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So you didn't mind if they left a bit uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No, I didn't mind. No, therefore, as I say, all of them, not one of them ever suffered with indigestion so I must have - not up 'til now they don't so - so it shows I fed them right didn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 They could, yes, if they wanted it and it was there to give it to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Could they ask for things to be passed to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did they have to hold their knife and fork and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh used to - except Edie - she would turn her spoon up the other way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were they able to bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Not while they were eating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When did they leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - usually when - time for school or
 - or - say now, come on, get ready for school, go and wash your hands before you go and - they'd go out to the scullery, wash their hands then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did they have to wait 'til everybody else had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh usually we finished - started and finished if we were all there together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you all sit at the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No - well to tell you - in the kitchen we had a tremendous - a big bay and we had a round table - there was no special was there - a round table, they sat anywhere. Except when Made was young, she had a - the high chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And you fed her in the high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. Oh, 'til she leaned to feed herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When your children were young did you feel that there was a right way or a wrong way to bring children up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I - I just followed the way we were brought up you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you and your husband have the same ideas about bringing children up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes, he never - well whatever I said he agreed to really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever talk about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I - 
he said he would have - he hoped that no - neither of his boys would have to - work like he had to work at piece work because it was - so - tearing - you know, took all the life of you - he - he said he hoped they wouldn't go in - well then they all wante
d
 to go - both of them wanted to go to sea so - I took my - as I say my elder brother's and my brother-in-law talked them out of it, they said, it's all right while you're young, you - you go out and you see the world but when once you marry there's no lif
e for you or your wife or your children. So - therefore - it finished them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you and your husband talk about the children much and decide and how you were going to treat them or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, I just - the only thing was when 
they left school we used to - I took them up to the Chamber of Commerce and got them to - have a slight examination - how far their education and then they would - you paid a fee that then if there was any body - would apply there to the Merchant - Mercha
n
t of Commerce for a junior or anything like that - that - even grown ups - they would try and place you - they kept that - art separate that you know that in London you'd have a certain - kind of education, well the first was Edie - let's see, Alec got hi
s
 from the - Librarian. We had a little one first where - when he was bombed - that's another tale, that don't interfere with you. He went there first and he didn't - after was bombed I wouldn't he was home for a while then I took him up the Chamber - no, 
he - he got it from the Chamber of Commerce then he went back and told - repaid the fee then he went to the Royal Statistical Society - I can't say it. And then Edith was the next. I took her - she got a - a job at Burroughs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396  Wel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 come - the big chemists in Sn
ow Hill, it's not there now is it. It was a wonderful place, she got wonderful training there. And she got on and - then they went to evening classes, I got them - after they left school they went to evening classes and she took up shorthand and typing an
d - she got on that she was the manager - the under manager's secretary you know. Used to take the notes down. But then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396 when the war was over this was d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 uring the first world war - when the war was over - he gave her a rise he says, now you'll have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
no - we w
on't - you'll have no more as long as you remain in the firm because we're - now filling the places with the men as they come home from the war, that's their tale. So Edith said, well - what shall I do. I said, well please yourself, you've got to look to 
your future and then she got this - I forget how she got this job at - the bank - the bank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 She got a job in a bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 That was a foreign bank - then. Swiss bank. And - it's up there yet - Ionian bank. I don't know if you hear of it. It's a very we
althy bank now and she got there that she went on and on 'til she was - she never went into the main part of the bank, she was always in the - the - secretary and manager's offices and she was there 'til her health gave way. And - oh, and then Madge went 
there, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 To the bank as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. They both were in the bank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Would only be mother that I'd go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You saw your mother very often didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well the latter part of her life she lived with me rally, lived together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And you asked her advice in bringing up your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. Yes, I al - and she never told me wrong advice. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You had the same ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What about your mother-in-law - did you see much of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
I didn't see a great deal of her but she was - she was scotch woman. I will say I like Scotch men but I don't like Scotch women. They're very hard. Well she - I never once had a - a difference with her all the time but I couldn't say I - I liked her.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ask her advice about the children? ;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. In fact she was like my husband, she didn't like children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, that's all I could do was to - do the best for them and - and when they started - out I encouraged them to bring their friends home.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you feel anything was particularly important in bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No - they used to go to Sunday 
school and that sort of thing and then as they got older they dropped - dropped out and - then - you know, didn't go so often. Alec - Alec and Arthur kept at the mission in East Ham, it's just been pulled down. That he - he did a lot for there to - minist
e
r said it was wicked to dance - to go to dances. Well as a young I used to - they used to dance at home but they never went out to public dances. But - then at that time Alec had his - had his friends and Edith had her friends from - from the - where she 
worked }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  Burroughs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396  We}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 lcome at that time and - you know, they used to - like - if they came - met - start playing the piano, they'd do a little dancing around like that and then when it come to birthdays we always had a - a nice party for them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You always had parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you want the children to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh they always did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well they've always been lovable towards me, I can't say anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 When the children were young did both you and your husband ever manage to leave them so you could go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I'll tell you what - how we used to manage. There was a woman that I used to have perhaps for - Tuesdays and Friday to do a bit of 
cleaning or anything, I'd ask her to come and stop if they were young but as Edie got older I - used to - light the - there was a gas bracket and I'd light the gas there and tell her not to touch it and say, we're going up to mother's or somewhere like th
at and - if Madge wakes give her a drink but she - Madge - and the boys never woke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 How old would Edie be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 She would be in - she was six - she was eight years older than Madge, see, so she was - when Made was about two she would be ten wouldn't s
he. But you know, you could trust her. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were you able to go out fairly regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No, very seldom. It might be round to my husband's sister, she had a family and they used to come round and - and - join in - the - on - evenings you know. Sh
e - she had her children, two of them who - one was very clever at the piano, oh both of them were but the girl had a very nice voice. So you see we had plenty of music as well as - singing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you let your children join in when grown-ups were tal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 ing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh I don't think so. Not into the conver - not 'til they were old enough to - know what they're talking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did you bri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396 ng them up to consider important}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - to - well to be - behave themselves as - and to - always say their prayers night and morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you tell them they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I don't think there was very much fighting amongst the children - only the school fights, I remember - going in with the - to - from one
 school to the other I don't know if he got in a fight with them then but there was never much school fighting really - never much squabbling with - children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was there any other children you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. 'Cos you see 
when - most of their time was in Barking Road - as I told you there was a bank at the corner and then the Modern Nautical Schools and then the piano - sold pianos and she used to teach - singing and playing, well she had one girl the same age as Edie and 
she had another one later near my Madge - just younger than Madgie, yes, younger than Madgie. Well she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
 the doctor - Doctor Hurley and - but they were - w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396 e - I used to have these - Joyc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
e Keys in my place when she was young, playing with Madge. And on this other side there was two children - Sylvia and Norman Frisby and then - they were quite - no, Fris - Sylvia - Sylvia was a naughty little girl - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396 squabbly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 . But the boy, Norman was a good boy. They - played with these and - then - then there was no mor
e children on the - right along. And then - then - you see when we came down here they were - grown up you might say so really no squabbling at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 If your children did something you disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh we'd talk it over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You told me once you smacked Madge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Ah that was - I think that's about the only - well it - I remembered it up to now. Did I ever tell you I had measles when I was thirty?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 That must have been painful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh I was ill. He - he brought - he'd h
ad - that was the second time he had measles, he brought it home. He - he hadn't gone to - had he gone to school? He - he may have gone to school I - no, he hadn't. He'd gone to a mission school - Sunday school. Whether it was there he brought it home I d
on't know but this was the second time he'd had it and oh dear, it - it wasn't so bad when it came out but it was - the time sickening for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your husband ever punish the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 If they were naughty what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh he'd - he'd talk to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were they sent to bed or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Oh - I - tell you one time, it was very seldom I left them only there was - a - I'd had the decorators in so - from the kitchen - of course I always had a - a guard ov
er the - over the fire in the kitchen so - we went - we moved into the front - the best room - the front room, that was in the small house in Compton Avenue. I brought the - the guard from there into the front room. Well see it was - in the kitchen was a 
k
itchener but in the front room was an open grate and - Alec got hold of a - a stick and - put it - through the bar of the guard and then - you know - make a flame. Well when - I'd only gone a little while - gone to get a message while - just before dad ca
m
e in. 'Course when he came in he could small smoke - fire and - and of course - I think he - well of course Edie tried to remonstrate with him and then - of course she was older than him and - anyhow - she told Peter and of course he - he - he'd brought h
o
me overcoat - he'd brought home overcoat up in town, not that I - he never - I wouldn't let - it was such a common looking thing I wouldn't let him have it but at the moment we'd - he'd tried it on and - as punishment he says, I'm going to take it back, y
o
u won't have the overcoat. So that was the only time that he - that he got cross and punished - he took the overcoat - anyhow the overcoat was a common thing so you know, these men, to make up their money - money would - try and get a kind of a - tally bu
siness among}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
the other men so Peter thought - saw this overcoat known I was wanting one for him he - he thought he'd bring it home. I says, you'll take it back. I choose me own clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Would you say that your children received the ideas they had about
 how to behave from both parents or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Oh - I don't think they would like to offend their dad. There was a little bit of fear - but we were always lovable, one to the other - the children - and I. They'd always obey me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Would you say that you had more influence on them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 In the district where you lived then who were considered the most important people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What - while they were children? Well you see how it was, o
pposite, before the gas works was built that was all fields. Then there was - a row of shops, a chemist a butchers, a greengrocers and Evans's the grocers that went right round the corner. On the right past those two turnings, Boundary Road and Central Pa
rk Road there was a big jewelers with - we were just on speaking terms but that we all - Keats there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was there any other families like yourself around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, only next door - the Frisby's. And then the - then it was Hamlets the estate agen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 s, they
 had a big place, it's still there I believe. Then there was another college - for - you know, like more of private tuition for - languages and shorthand and that. But that closed up during wartime. And then there was another big doctors at the corner - s
o -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So you lived in a little group of shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Place of our - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have a struggle to make ends meet or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I tell you - one time I had a - awful shock. Was - I used to pay 
rent - and - when the - that was including I think about eighteen shillings a week, I think that was all in - with the rates included see, then the landlord - arranged that. Well after the war - or during the war the rates start going up and up and up 'ti
l
 I paid more in rates - well I didn't do it but - she - the - well it was she or he, I forget now said that - that I could pay so much a rent and pay me own taxes. So - the - taxes - used - rates or whatever - come to more than what I paid rent in the end
.
 But that was all right, I was quite willing to pay if I'd been notified. But - they never told me until the agents that was doing he business that I got a - a demand notice with a so many days to pay. I - I knew I would have to do but I was waiting to ge
t
 a notice, which I never did. Well at that time dad was - you know, on a bad time with the piecework and I hadn't got very much money, but I managed to get it some way or the other. I - paid it - but that time until - I don't suppose they would have come 
down on me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever see the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Not the man himself, no. Agent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have much to do with the local shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - Dennis, they were very nicely. She used to come over and chat now and again and - she would - when o
ne of them was queer she brought over new laid eggs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Who were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
That - butcher's wife. They owned all that block of shops - they were well - very well' to - do the Denis's. And the - chemist - the name of Wilson, he was very nice. He came ov
er and tried to fit my mother with glasses but of course her age - eyes were going. He brought over and tried to test her eyes while she was in bed, yes, so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 So they were quite friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Very - quite nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You said that you had a party when your children had a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Can you remember anything you did together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Oh we always get up Christmas Day but - we didn't have many - visitors so much on Christmas Day but next day - friends - cousins and that always come and my sister used to come with her two children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have a piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were there any other musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 He - he had a violin when he was young but he didn't carry on with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did any of you sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well both of - in fact - all of them did. Madge as well - Madge had a very pretty contralto voice. Edie was more - more soprano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever make music together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. As I say, the cousins - on - the dad's side, they used to - they were all musical
, they used to come and as I say they - they'd have set dances and all that sort of thing, you know when there was the - there was no doors you see, made one great big room of it - pulled the curtains back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 That's how they amused themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 And
 then as they grew older and were going to dances - like say the - others Hockey club would have a - a - dance now and gain well there'd be the two girls and two boys you see, my two boys and the two girls they'd all go in a party. Or else there'd be anot
her girl friend - she went out to America, she - she'd join their party and a boy but you know they never went to public dances but they'd go to these sort and I've told you didn't I about Peoples Palace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 About you and the Peoples Palace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 The Peo
ples Palace used to have dances for - the students or anything and we used to go up and watch the - I used to go up and watch them down below dancing. It - did you - put that - you didn't do that did you on there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 That was you used to do that not your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. No. That - well they - they used to go to those dances because as they improved they had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  winter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
gardens built at the side - the Scotch dances, Caledonian school used to - do you know Caledonian Schools? Well - they - had - used to hold the dances there. Anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever play games with your children? Did your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, we'd be in with them, we wouldn't keep them apart - wouldn't keep apart but we'd as I say when my niece start - got tired of playing t
he piano I used to - two or three little simple waltzes or something like that that I remembered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were there books and magazines and newspapers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Where did you get them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well there was a - a - a corner shop in Boundary road. Used to deliver them or we could go out the back way and get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you belong to a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you read aloud to each other or to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No - no, my oldest sister did when we were young but I never did - I don't know, I never had time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were the children taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
The only - the only times was - one time - the kiddies were queer at Christmastime so when it was my Madgie's - no, when she was a year old I was goi
ng up to my sister's when my mother was keeping house and there was - we went up - I took her - all my four up and there was three - three from my sister-in-law's, that was seven and - Willie was eight but do you know, as it happened they had some - when 
w
e got three - going to be there for tea - the - there was somebody very important come to visit my sister, well she didn't want a tribe of kids so we got the girl - she used to keep a maid then - took them out and give them their tea in the kitchen. But -
 and then in the evening time there was - dancing with these elder ones - they'd come from Scotland and - we shoved the kiddi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
s in - it was a square bay - we shoved the kiddies in there to look on and do you know there wasn't a murmur with those children. Behaved themselves the whole time, it was - instead of a children's party it was a grown ups party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you often take them to visit relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Not - not very often, no, not the four of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were they taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No. Only when I'm
 buying them clothes or anything liked that. I tell you what we do on Sunday we - well they were getting grown up then - we - see the buses were outside as I told you - forty bus to Wanstead - we'd go - take them - we'd all go on - dad as well. I've got a
 photo of that - see dad. Sitting - we were sitting on a log. Yes. And - we'd take a - I'd take food in a basket and - have - you know, sunny weather. But that's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I did - well of course as you know I did before I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  and then we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  - friends of ours lived at H}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10038344\charrsid2379396 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
stings and we used to go down there. Dad and I. We'd send the children - they - the children always - I always saw that they had a holidays. Sometimes send them up to Liverpool 
when - when my brother had a big house there. He would - him and all in turn. They were only too pleased to have - they had no children of their own you see. They would have a holiday and dad and I might have a fort - a week or a fortnight down at Hasting
s - I was glad to get back, I - I liked to be in me own home. One - one year we went to Leigh, that's just before you get to Southend, that was a nice holiday. Nice quiet hol - I had a week, that was enough.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 But you didn't all go together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did the children put on different clothes on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you think it wrong to work or enjoy yourself on on a Sunday or that it didn't matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well I - we used to - I didn't like to do work on Sunday, not - I like to k
eep it as quiet as possible and - my - when my oldest sister was here she used to like to go to any of these - I - when I was young I went with her to hear Doctor Barnardo - you've heard of - and I saw him - very few people can ever remember seeing Doctor
 
Barnardo - he - there was - in one of his big - he had a very big place as the back of - Burdett Road and - it was the Harvest Festival and it was the children, all the - was in the galleries and we went there and that was the - I - I can remember it quit
e well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your children go as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No, they were - I wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396  then. And then another time we went to the City Temple. That was bombed wasn't it? Where is City Temple? Alec.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were they allowed to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Yes. Not regular. When - as children up to I grew - go into me teens we used to go to the Congregational chapel in Picket Street Limehouse, that's off Burdett Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 But when you had your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Well, yes - well - when - when - in Goff Street they were too young. When we come to East Ham they went to a mission didn't you - and - and then attended that mission in East ham. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your husband go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh he - he was a great one for missio
n in the af - Sunday afternoon for men only. And then - he - he used to take - mother to chapel - church or whichever you call it. Not a constant one - didn't belong thoroughly into one but he used - as I say, wed'd go together, sometimes - if we couldn't
 leave the house he'd take mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 I haven't got a voice - you can tell that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did the church run any temperance clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Not when I grew up - I was bad - sign the pledge when I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your children go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did they go to any family services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
No, I don't think - I didn't keep them - I let them - every - like Edith's mother belonged to Church of England and Edith was baptised in a church therefore I gave her th
e chance as - I sent her to a church school - a church - Sunday school and to the evening ser - or morning service and - I let her take Madge when - but she didn't like it at all. She said, no, I like the mission best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes. While they were young but - we did up to - dad would just Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Were your children taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Who taught them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well - I think I did - told you about the first family, my father -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Your children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh my children. Oh - well I did the same to them and - and dad used to too 'til they got old enough to say them themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 After you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8463588 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
 did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 What were his views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 
Scotch Radical. Well, you know, he was a proper Liberal really he always used to vote Liberal ad then - one or two tricks the Liberal sided with the - the Conservatives but - he went more to Labour when
 Labour started, he - he - went more Labour the latter part of his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you or your husband vote in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Did you as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Yes, I should have voted. I forget how we voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You can't remember who you voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Oh I wouldn't do - wouldn't vote for Conservative. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Why wouldn't you vote Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3160330 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 Well 'cos I remember quite well when they - somebody - the Liberals -was no Labour then - Liberals put up - that - for the
 old people over seventy should have a pension of five shillings a week. And it was turned down, they said, no. The people would spoil them - what was it - as - stop them being thirsty - if they had a pension of five shillings a week it stop them being th
rifty, they should - work and save. Now I told you about the - the type of a working man which was a high class working man and he - what time did he to bring up a family. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023217 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9327244\charrsid2379396 You mean he didn't have enough to save?
\par 
